These 6 stocks in the S&P 500 are down at least 50% — and analysts say buy

By Philip van Doorn

Published: May 31, 2019 8:57 a.m. ET

Share

Overall, 14 stocks among the S&P 500 are down at least 50% from their 52-week highs

By

Philipvan Doorn

Investing columnist

May has been a reversal for what has otherwise been a good 2019 for U.S. stocks which are briefly surpassed the all-time closing high reached before the coronavirus pandemic, propelled by surging which helps them to get more information about the US share market and other share market of European Union. Each company has a different story, of course, which you must understand as part of your own research if you wish to do some “bottom feeding.”

For example, you might have a particular opinion about the (potential) resolution of the trade conflict between the U.S. and China, and its timing. Michael Brush is a Manhattan-based financial writer who publishes the stock newsletter Brush Up on Stocks. Brush has covered business for the New York Times and The Economist group, for one, believes it’s time to invest in many good stocks and other semiconductor stocks and other select industries in anticipation of a trade agreement.
